'''Deniz Daniel Gül''' (born 2 July 2004) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[FC Porto|Porto]]. Born in Sweden, he plays for the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].

==Early life==
Born and raised in Stockholm, to a Turkish father and Swedish mother, Gül started to play football with local club Stuvsta IF. He later went on to represent [[Segeltorps IF]], [[IF Brommapojkarna]], [[AIK Fotboll|AIK]] and FC Djursholm at youth level.<ref>{{cite web|title=Spelare kallade till distriktslagssamlingar|url=https://www.svenskalag.se/fcd/nyheter/1420940/spelare-kallade-till-distriktslagssamlingar|publisher=FC Djursholm|date=20 December 2019|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Spelare kallade till regionalt läger|url=https://www.svenskalag.se/fcd/nyheter/1433317/spelare-kallade-till-regionalt-lager|publisher=FC Djursholm|date=23 January 2020|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref name="unicoach">{{cite web|title=Güls målform i Hammarby bakom fint Unicoachpris|url=https://unicoach.se/2022/11/guls-malform-i-hammarby-bakom-fint-unicoachpris/|publisher=Unicoach|date=14 November 2022|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title="Varför? Vet inte – jag bara gör mål"– Fotboll Sthlm möter Deniz Gül|url=https://fotbollsthlm.se/hammarby/varfor-vet-inte-jag-bara-gor-mal-fotboll-sthlm-moter-deniz-gul/|publisher=Fotboll STHLM|date=1 December 2022|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref>

In 2021, Gül joined the youth academy of [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]].<ref>{{cite web|title=P17-landslaget: Deniz Gül och Marcus Rafferty kallade till läger|url=https://www.gamlahammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/p17-landslaget-deniz-gul-och-marcus-rafferty-kallade-till-lager/|publisher=[[Hammarby Fotboll]]|date=16 November 2021|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=P18-landslaget: Deniz Gül till samling på Bosön|url=https://www.gamlahammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/p18-landslaget-deniz-gul-till-samling-pa-boson/|publisher=[[Hammarby Fotboll]]|date=22 February 2022|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Spelare att hålla koll på i P17 Allsvenskan: "En artist"|url=https://unicoach.se/2021/06/spelare-att-halla-koll-pa-i-p17-allsvenskan-en-artist/|publisher=Unicoach|date=4 June 2021|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Spelare att hålla koll på i P19 Allsvenskan 2022|url=https://unicoach.se/2022/04/spelare-att-halla-koll-pa-i-p19-allsvenskan-2022/|publisher=Unicoach|date=2 April 2022|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref> In August 2022, Gül reportedly turned down a move to Italian club [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Spelet bakom AIK:s sparkning av Grzelak|url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/allsvenskan/spelet-bakom-aiks-sparkning-av-grzelak/|publisher=[[Expressen]]|date=23 August 2022|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref> He won the 2022 [[P19 Allsvenskan]] with Hammarby, becoming the league's top scorer and being voted Forward of the Year.<ref name="unicoach"/><ref>{{cite web|title=Deniz Gül korad till Årets Anfallare i P19-Allsvenskan|url=https://www.gamlahammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/deniz-gul-korad-till-arets-anfallare-i-p19-allsvenskan/|publisher=[[Hammarby Fotboll]]|date=13 November 2022|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Hammarby===
On 17 September 2022, Gül was called up to Hammarby's senior squad in [[Allsvenskan]] for the first time, but remained on the bench the whole game in a 1–1 away draw against [[BK Häcken]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Truppen mot BK Häcken|url=https://www.gamlahammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/truppen-mot-bk-hacken-13/|publisher=[[Hammarby Fotboll]]|date=17 September 2022|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref> In January 2023, he signed a three-year contract with Hammarby.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://fotbollsthlm.se/hammarby/sa-byggs-nya-hammarby-har-tittat-pa-rb-salzburg-och-nordsjalland/|title=Så byggs nya Hammarby: "Har tittat på RB Salzburg och Nordsjälland"|date=20 January 2023|accessdate=24 October 2023|publisher=Fotboll Sthlm|language=Swedish}}</ref> Throughout the 2023 season, Gül mostly played for feeder team [[Hammarby Talang FF|Hammarby TFF]] in [[Ettan Fotboll|Ettan]], Sweden's third tier, scoring 14 goals in 22 appearances.<ref name="profile">{{cite web |title=Deniz Gül |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/spelarfakta/deniz-gul/7fc92216-be0a-4800-8a76-442fcf791ba9/ |accessdate=24 October 2023 |publisher=[[Swedish Football Association]] |language=Swedish}}</ref> On 22 October 2023, he made his league debut for Hammarby in Allsvenskan, coming on as a substitute in a 0–0 draw against [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgårdens IF]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Chansfattigt, käbbligt och mållöst höstderby|url=https://www.gamlahammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/chansfattigt-kabbligt-och-mallost-hostderby/|publisher=[[Hammarby Fotboll]]|date=22 October 2023|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Stora orden om Deniz Gül: "Kommer bli riktigt bra"|url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/allsvenskan/stora-orden-om-deniz-gul-kommer-bli-riktigt-bra/|publisher=[[Expressen]]|date=23 October 2023|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Deniz Gül fick debutera mot Djurgården: "Nervös? Faktiskt inte"|url=https://fotbollsthlm.se/hammarby/deniz-gul-fick-debutera-mot-djurgarden-nervos-faktiskt-inte/|publisher=Fotboll STHLM|date=23 October 2023|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bajen-debutanten inspireras av nära vännen Erabi: "Stolt"|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/allsvenskan/bajen-debutanten-inspireras-av-nara-vannen-erabi-stolt/|publisher=Fotbollskanalen|date=23 October 2023|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref>

===Porto===
On 24 August 2024, Gül signed for Portuguese club [[FC Porto]] with a contract until 2029.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Oficial: Deniz Gül é reforço do FC Porto |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/fc-porto/detalhe/oficial-deniz-gul-e-reforco-do-fc-porto |access-date=24 August 2024 |website=www.record.pt |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

On 25 September 2024, he made his continental debut in his career against [[FK Bodø/Glimt|Bodø/Glimt]] in a [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League#League phase|UEFA Europa League]] away game and also scored his first continental goal, they lost 3-2.

On 29 September 2024, he made [[Primeira Liga]] debut as a substitute and scored his first league goal with the team against [[FC Arouca|Arouca]] in a 4-0 home win. On 8 December 2024, he played with Porto B in [[Liga Portugal 2]] against [[G.D. Chaves|Chaves]]. On 31 October 2024, he made his [[Taça da Liga|Allianz Cup]] debut as a starter against [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]], they won 2-0.

On 19 June 2025, he played as a substitute against [[Inter Miami]] in a [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]] game.

==International career==
In 2023, Gül was called up to the [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|Swedish U19s]], making appearances in the [[2023 UEFA European Under-19 Championship qualification]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sverige förlorade svängig match|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2023/03/p1904-swe-cze/|publisher=[[Swedish Football Association]]|date=28 March 2023|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sent mål sänkte Sverige|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2023/03/p19-por-swe/|publisher=[[Swedish Football Association]]|date=22 March 2023|accessdate=24 October 2023|language=Swedish}}</ref>

On 6 November 2024, Gül announced he would instead represent Turkey internationally despite having made a dozen appearances for Sweden.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Klart: Deniz Gül byter landslag |url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/sverige/klart-deniz-gul-byter-landslag/ |access-date=2024-11-08 |website=fotbollskanalen |language=sv}}</ref>

On 14 March 2025, Gül was called up by [[Vincenzo Montella]] to the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]] for the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League promotion/relegation play-offs]] against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=47025 |title=A Millî Takımımızın Macaristan Maçları Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |website=TFF.org |access-date=14 March 2025 |date=14 March 2025 |language=tr}}</ref>

On 18 November 2025, he scored his first national goal against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]].<ref name="tffgoal">{{Cite web |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=49064 |title=Bileti Mart'ta Alacağız, Teşekkürler Bizim Çocuklar! İSPANYA 2-2 TÜRKİYE |website=TFF.org |access-date=18 November 2025 |date=18 November 2025 |language=tr}}</ref>

